bio.content: Originally from Mt. Gambier SA, Dave Graney delivers smooth sounds via an eclectic range of jazz/r&b derived chordal voicings that are forever ahead of the chasing pack, rendering his unique leather clad sound timeless. Based in Melbourne Australia. Constantly touring Australia nationally. Dave Graney and the Lurid yellow Mist are Dave Graney Electric gtr vocals, Clare Moore rums vocals, Stu Thomas bass vocals, Stuart Perera, Electric gtr and vocals. "1001 Australian nights" a memoir of his music life was published on Affirm press in 2011. Dave Graney Discography (retrospectively) You've Been in my Mind (Dave Graney and the MistLY album, Cockaigne, 2012). Rock'n'roll is where I hide (Dave Graney and the Lurid Yellow Mist,Album, LIBERATION,2011) Supermodified (Cockaigne/Fuse,Album, 2010) Knock yourself out (Dave Graney,ALBUM, Cockaigne/Fuse,2009) We Wuz Curious (The Lurid Yellow Mist ....featuring Dave Graney and Clare Moore. ALBUM , Illustrious Artists , July 2008) Rock Formations ( SALMON, Bang Records, cd and double vinyl, 2007) Keepin’ it Unreal (Dave Graney and Clare Moore ...featuring Stu D aka le Comte d’Alucard) Cockaigne/Reverberation 2006) Hashish and Liquor Dave Graney and Clare Moore.Double cd on Cockaigne/Reverberation. 2005 Night of the wolverine (Dave Graney 'n' the Coral Snakes, re-issue plus 6 extra tracks from later on……..Cockaigne 2004) The Brother Who Lived (the Royal Dave Graney Show, Cockaigne 2003) The Soundtrack to the Movie Bad Eggs (David Graney and Clare Moore, Liberation, 2003) Two Fisted Art (the Moodists 1980 86….Wminc,2003) Heroic Blues (the Dave Graney Show, Cockaigne 2002) The Third Woman (Clare Moore solo CD, Chapter Music 2001) Kiss Tomorrow Goodbye (the Dave Graney Show, Cockaigne 2000) The Baddest ( Dave Graney ‘n’ the Coral Snakes best of collection 1999.Universal) The Dave Graney Show (the Dave Graney Show, Festival 1998) The Devil Drives (Dave Graney ‘n’ the Coral Snakes, Universal 1997) The Soft'n'Sexy Sound (Dave Graney ‘n’ the Coral Snakes, Universal 1995) You wanna be there but you don’t wanna travel (Dave Graney ‘n’ the Coral Snakes, Universal 1994) Night of the wolverine (Dave Graney ‘n’ the Coral Snakes, Universal 1993) Lure of the tropics (Dave Graney ‘n’ the Coral Snakes, Torn and Frayed 1992) I was the hunter and I was the prey (Dave Graney with the Coral Snakes, Fire 1992) Codine ( Dave Graney with the White Buffaloes . 12’ vinyl ep, Fire 1990. My life on the plains (Dave Graney with White Buffaloes, 1990) Double Life (the Moodists, lp, 1985) Thirstys Calling (the Moodists, lp, 1984) Engine Shudder (the Moodists, lp, AuGoGo 1982) Gone Dead/Chads Car ( 7’ 45 single ,AuGoGo 1981) Where the trees walk downhill ( 7’ 45 single , Au GoGo1980) Read more on Last.fm.
